# VibeGuard secure-by-default rules (Cursor)
# Stack: Next.js + Supabase. Satisfy every rule by construction; never weaken a control to make code run.

ALWAYS:
- Never hardcode/inline secrets; read from env. Never expose Supabase service_role, Stripe secret, or OpenAI keys to the client; only anon/publishable keys are public. (VG-007, VG-008)
- Authorize every read and write by ownership; deny by default; enable Supabase RLS with per-user policies; use non-guessable IDs. (VG-002, VG-003)
- Parameterized queries / ORM only — never string-concat SQL. Keep auto-escaping on; avoid dangerouslySetInnerHTML/v-html. Never pass user input to a shell as a string. Never unsafe-deserialize untrusted data. (VG-011..VG-014)
- Set security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options) and CSRF tokens + SameSite cookies on state-changing routes. (VG-018)
- Never log secrets/PII or full requests; keep tokens out of URLs. (VG-016)
- Pass only explicit DTO fields to Client Components; never whole server objects/config. (VG-010)
- Verify a package exists before importing; pin via lockfile; prefer current versions. (VG-020)
- Rate-limit auth and costly endpoints; re-validate server-side; never trust client validation alone. (VG-019)

WHEN AUTH IS PRESENT:
- Auth/authorization on the server; client holds only a post-verification session token. (VG-001)
- Hash passwords with Argon2id or bcrypt cost>=12; never plaintext/md5/sha1. (VG-006)
- Short-lived rotating sessions, invalidated on logout; tokens in HttpOnly+Secure+SameSite cookies, never localStorage. (VG-004, VG-015)
- No default credentials; no debug/test routes in production. (VG-005, VG-009)

WHEN PII/IDENTITY/PAYMENTS/HEALTH:
- Minimize data to third parties (DPA per processor); ship a delete endpoint + retention for PII fields. (VG-017)

BEFORE FINISHING:
- List the rules that applied and confirm each detect condition is absent. Functional != production-safe.
